A '''bill of entry''', abbreviated '''B/E''', is an account of [[Good (economics and accounting)|goods]] entered at a [[Customs House]], for [[International trade|import]]s and [[export]]s, detailing the merchant, quantity of goods, their type, and place of origin or destination.

